x25wanAdmnTable.name: x25wanAdmnTable
x25wanAdmnTable.description: The x25 WAN Admn table contains an entry for each manageable X.25 Subnet in the chassis. It provides a means to configure serial interface associated with the subnet.

x25wanAdmnEntry.name: x25wanAdmnEntry
x25wanAdmnEntry.description: There is one x25 WAN Cfg entry per x.25 subnet in the NAS chassis.

x25wanAdmnIndex.name: x25wanAdmnIndex
x25wanAdmnIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 Subnet in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 Subnet's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

x25wanAdmnType.name: x25wanAdmnType
x25wanAdmnType.description: Defines which physical serial interface type is implemented.

x25wanAdmnSpeed.name: x25wanAdmnSpeed
x25wanAdmnSpeed.description: Defines the serial port speed used in applications where the Gateway NAC generates a clock. This object will not effect the clock speed when the host provides the clock source. Default=57600.

x25wanAdmnLinkAvailable.name: x25wanAdmnLinkAvailable
x25wanAdmnLinkAvailable.description: Defines whether the WAN interface looks at DCD rather than DSR to determine that the physical layer is active.

x25wanAdmnClockSouce.name: x25wanAdmnClockSouce
x25wanAdmnClockSouce.description: Determines the source of the synchronous data clock.

x25wanAdmnMaxFrmSize.name: x25wanAdmnMaxFrmSize
x25wanAdmnMaxFrmSize.description: Determines the maximum received frame size allowed on the X.25 WAN. Default=300.

x25wanStatsTable.name: x25wanStatsTable
x25wanStatsTable.description: The x25wanStatsTable is composed of counters which allow the operator to view activity which can indicate the health of the WAN connection.

x25wanStatsEntry.name: x25wanStatsEntry
x25wanStatsEntry.description: There is one X.25 WAN status entry for each x.25 subnet installed in the NAS chassis.

x25wanStatsIndex.name: x25wanStatsIndex
x25wanStatsIndex.description: A unique value for each X25 WAN port in the NAS chassis. The value of this index matches is the entity index associated with this X25 subnet found in the USR Chassis MIB.

x25wanStatsGoodFramesTxs.name: x25wanStatsGoodFramesTxs
x25wanStatsGoodFramesTxs.description: A count of the number of good frames transmitted since this entity was initialized.

x25wanStatsGoodFramesRxs.name: x25wanStatsGoodFramesRxs
x25wanStatsGoodFramesRxs.description: A count of the good frames received since this entity was intitalized.

x25wanStatsTxUnderruns.name: x25wanStatsTxUnderruns
x25wanStatsTxUnderruns.description: A count of the number of transmit underruns that have been seen by this entity since initialization.

x25wanStatsRxOverruns.name: x25wanStatsRxOverruns
x25wanStatsRxOverruns.description: The number of receiver overruns detected by this entity since intitialization.

x25wanStatsRxCrcErrs.name: x25wanStatsRxCrcErrs
x25wanStatsRxCrcErrs.description: The number of received crc errors since this entity was intitialized.

x25wanStatsRxFrameNoBufs.name: x25wanStatsRxFrameNoBufs
x25wanStatsRxFrameNoBufs.description: The number of times this entity has recieved data without a buffer to place it into.

x25wanStatsUnrecoveredRxs.name: x25wanStatsUnrecoveredRxs
x25wanStatsUnrecoveredRxs.description: The number of overrun frames that the entity was unable to recover.

x25wanStatsRxOverflows.name: x25wanStatsRxOverflows
x25wanStatsRxOverflows.description: The number of receive buffer overflows seen by this entity since initialization.

x25wanStatsRxAborts.name: x25wanStatsRxAborts
x25wanStatsRxAborts.description: The number of recieve frame aborts seen by this entity since initialization.

x25wanStatsRxTooLongs.name: x25wanStatsRxTooLongs
x25wanStatsRxTooLongs.description: The number of frames recieved that exceeded the defined maximum receive frame size.

x25wanStatsTxTooShorts.name: x25wanStatsTxTooShorts
x25wanStatsTxTooShorts.description: The number of times that the upper protocol layers attempted to transmit too small a frame.

x25wanStatsRxTooShorts.name: x25wanStatsRxTooShorts
x25wanStatsRxTooShorts.description: A count of the number of frames received that were smaller than the minimum frame size.

x25wanStatsTxBadPackets.name: x25wanStatsTxBadPackets
x25wanStatsTxBadPackets.description: The number of bad packets that the WAN interface received for transmission from the upper layers of the X.25 protocol stack.

x25wanStatsTxRingQFulls.name: x25wanStatsTxRingQFulls
x25wanStatsTxRingQFulls.description: A count of the number of times the circular buffer used for transmission was full when a transmission was attempted by the upper layers of the X.25 protocol stack.

x25wanStatsRxRingQSize.name: x25wanStatsRxRingQSize
x25wanStatsRxRingQSize.description: A number that indicates the received circular queue size on the X.25 WAN.

x25wanStatsDSR.name: x25wanStatsDSR
x25wanStatsDSR.description: X.25 WAN interface DSR signal status.

x25wanStatsCTS.name: x25wanStatsCTS
x25wanStatsCTS.description: X.25 WAN interface CTS signal status.

x25wanStatsDCD.name: x25wanStatsDCD
x25wanStatsDCD.description: X.25 WAN interface DCD signal status.

x25wanTrapEnaTable.name: x25wanTrapEnaTable
x25wanTrapEnaTable.description: The x25 WAN Trap Enable table contains an entry for each manageable X.25 Subnet in the chassis. It provides a means to enable reporting of traps associated with the subnet.

x25wanTrapEnaEntry.name: x25wanTrapEnaEntry
x25wanTrapEnaEntry.description: There is one x25 WAN Cfg entry per x.25 subnet in the NAS chassis.

x25wanTrapEnaIndex.name: x25wanTrapEnaIndex
x25wanTrapEnaIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 Subnet in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 Subnet's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

x25wanTrapEnaOutOfSvc.name: x25wanTrapEnaOutOfSvc
x25wanTrapEnaOutOfSvc.description: Enables generation of a trap when the WAN port status changes from Link Active to Out Of Service.

x25wanTrapEnaLinkActive.name: x25wanTrapEnaLinkActive
x25wanTrapEnaLinkActive.description: Enables generation of a trap when the WAN port status changes from Out Of Service to Link Active.
